args: Out on patrol, Luca? 'Preciate it!\nOh, is Chelsea not with you today?
You two've been joined at the hip\never since Valentine's Day.
We, uh, kinda got into it yesterday...
It's not like that, man. I just...\nI might've been a little harsh on her.
But I don't want her risking her neck just\nto get me some present, and if you don't\ntalk to her bluntly, she never listens.
Anyway, what's done is done.\nIt had to be said.
Uh-huh. Well, if you think ya had to, ya\nhad to. You wanna go a couple rounds?\nKnock you right outta that funk?
Ooh, great idea! It's been too long.\nAll righty. Let's rumble!
Hnnngh... Ahhh! I'm stiff as a board after\nall that sparring. Hope my bed's ready for\nthe belly flop of the centur—
Gah! Chelsea?\nUhhh... What brings you here?
And why is my room A DISASTER AREA?!
Oh, this? You said you didn't want any of\nmy presents, so I'm disposing of them.
Every single gift I gave you for Valentine's\nDay was just in your way, Luccy.
And anything in my Luccy's way has to\nbe deleted. Delete... Delete... Delete!\nAha ha... AHA HA HA HA HA HA HA!
Is this about what I said yesterday?\nLook, I didn't mean I don't want all the\nstuff you gave me; I only—
You don't have to explain anything, Luccy.\nYou always sacrifice yourself for others.\nBut what you don't want, you don't want!
And anything my Luccy doesn't want gets\nDE-LE-TED!
Er, Chelsea? Chelsea!\nWhere are you going?! Wait!
*huff...* *pant...* Chelsea!\nWait, you gave me that! Don't burn it!
Why not, sweetie? If you don't need it,\nthen neither does this world.
All those fun Valentine's memories...\nAll those happy Valentine's dreams...\nThey're aaaaall gone now.
But that's just fine. If it's going to get in\nthe way of my Luccy loving me, Valentine's\nDay can rot in the gutter and DIE!
Don't say that! There's nothing wrong with\nfeeling sentimental about a holiday.
Nobody's telling you not to.\nI'M certainly not telling you not to!
But that's the thing, Luccy.\nIf you hate it, it isn't fun for me at all.\nThat's why I'm reducing it all to ash!
Chelsea... Everything I say to you truly\ngoes in one ear and out the other, huh?
Well, I'm not letting it slide. Not anymore.\nI'm about two seconds away from going\nFULL LUCA SMASH!
Damn right I'm mad. I'm not just gonna\nsit here and watch you trample your own\nfeelings right in front of me!
PLEASE. Just listen to me for once.\nActually listen. What I said yesterday...
I meant that I don't want a present from\nyou that causes you to come home bruised\nand battered!
I'm not telling you I hate presents. I hate\nseeing you go too far. That's it. That's all.\nI don't want to see you get hurt, Chelsea.
But...sometimes you have to go just a little\nbit crazy to really show how you fee—
Is that what love is to you—madness?!\nObsession? Rare, expensive gifts? NO!
Your feelings shouldn't come\nwrapped up in a box.
Your feelings are inside you, Chelsea.\nIn your heart!
That's all I need from you.\nOkay? That's enough for me!
Am I getting through to you? Those are\nMY feelings. Did they get across okay?
I love you SO much, but...I wasn't really\nlistening to what you were telling me.
I completely missed how kind you were\nbeing.
Gah! HOT! Maybe don't glomp me with\na lit torch in your hands!
AUGH, STOP! IT BURNS!\nGimme that, you dang lunatic!
Er... Your Highness, there's been a minor\nconflagration in the courtyard.
Yes, well. It seems Chelsea was trying to\nburn some refuse there...
Just some scorched grass, thankfully. It\nwas just a small blaze, quickly contained.\nShall we make a formal reprimand?
If no harm came from it, there's no need.\nHonestly, something of this scale\nhardly surprises me at this point.
If I yelled every time someone set the\nyard aflame with magic or blew it up\nwith some ancient weapon, I'd go hoarse.
You...have a point. Understood.\nThen I'll take no further action.
How does today's apple pie taste,\non a scale of ＂one＂ to ＂nummy＂?
Tee hee hee... Okay, one more bite, then!\n＂Aaaaah!＂
(There's no better present I can\ngive Luccy than my feelings.)
(And that's something I can give him\nevery day—not just on Valentine's!)
(I hope you've got room for a whole lot\nmore, my sweet.)
('Cause I've got so, so, so, so, so, so, so,\nso, so, so, so, so, so, so, so, so, so, so, so,\nSO, SO, SO, SO, SO, SO, SO, SO, SO...)
